<h1>Problem 669 - 2015 IMOSL, N4, N</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 8</h2>
<p>Suppose that \(a_0, a_1, \dots\) and \(b_0, b_1, \dots\) are two sequences of positive integers such that \(a_0, b_0 \ge 2\) and \[a_{n+1} = \gcd{(a_n, b_n)} + 1, \qquad b_{n+1} = \operatorname{lcm}{(a_n, b_n)} - 1.\] Show that the sequence \(a_n\) is eventually periodic; in other words, there exist integers \(N \ge 0\) and \(t > 0\) such that \(a_{n+t} = a_n\) for all \(n \ge N\).</p>
